          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-12-04 14:21:13.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-03-25 12:59:25.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-6235 osd-ldiskfs: NOT skip LMAC_NOT_IN_OI in osd_check_lma",
        "message": "LU-6235 osd-ldiskfs: NOT skip LMAC_NOT_IN_OI in osd_check_lma\n\nSometimes, the ost-object may references a wrong indoe because of\nthe invalid OI mapping. Usually, the OSD can auto detect that via\nosd_check_lma(). For old system, if the inode's LMV contains flag\nLMAC_NOT_IN_OI, it would skip related checking. But such behavior\nis wrong, if may cause the osd-object to reference some important\nsystem inode, and cause system crash via subsequent modification.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ib5cdf2ee4d9893a87fde3caf81109eabdad9ecfa\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/13922\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Lai Siyao <lai.siyao@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Liang Zhen <liang.zhen@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
